16/11/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Monday (November 16th) the arrest of a dangerous inmate who escaped from prison by helicopter earlier this year.
Albanian Alket Rizaj, a convicted murderer, was recaptured north of Athens early Monday.
He escaped Greece's biggest prison aboard a helicopter on February 22nd along with bank robber Vassilis Paleokostas, who remains on the run.
(AP, DPA - 16/11/09)
